name: The Looking Glass
description:
Beckoned by the other side..

I went on a walk with the intention to find a magical spot, and came across this oddly-placed house and the sidewalk in front of it where this unassuming mirror was positioned. It felt like it was disconnected from time, with the front yard having a few patches of dead grasses & weeds and mostly dirt, and all the other houses around it seeming way more alive or normal, per se; like the cliche strange house found in a typical neighborhood that looked like it could be haunted or be housing witches.

As with the mirror, it was only later when I looked over the pictures that I realized just how on point that spot was to my intention, seeing how as I was looking around, I was also being peered at through the looking glass.

In this image, I also hid my signature more than a few times as almost like a "Where's Waldo" watermark.
